<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09149c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09149c">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09149c"> 149(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> true for him</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">They sing a song about it, a song with a true gleam of African poetry: <br>&ldquo;<i>Oh! Livingstone Tree! <br>Oh! Livingstone Tree! <br>Wherefore dost thou jut out <br>So lonely and sharply on <br>The fire-swept moors?&rdquo; <br>Answer from Tree: <br>&ldquo;Jutting out lonely? <br>Oh no! Oh no! <br>I am waiting for the King <br>To overtake me! Waiting! <br>Waiting for the King to come!</i>&rdquo; <br><mark>True for you</mark>, St. Paul, &ldquo;the whole creation groaneth&mdash;waiting for &hellip;&rdquo; <small> Dan Crawford, <a name="BTLG1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BTLG1"><cite title="source">Back to the Long Grass</cite></a> (1923) 77</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
